classes.name: Vector
classes.docstring:
A math-like vector.

Represents an n-dimensional numeric vector. ``Vector`` objects support
vector addition and subtraction, scalar multiplication and division,
negation, rounding, and comparison tests.

methods.name: length
methods.docstring: Return the length of the vector. Equivalent to abs(vector).

methods.name: normalized
methods.docstring: Return the normalized vector of the vector.

methods.name: dot
methods.docstring:
Performs vector dot product, returning the sum of
``a[0] * b[0], a[1] * b[1], ...``

methods.name: isclose
methods.docstring: Return True if the vector is close to another Vector.
